what it is: a function inside roblox that gets the base pointer for tls (thread local storage) for the current running thread

what its used for: TLS basically holds thread-specific data including the identity structure we just talked about in https://github.com/LockaSkids/Roblox-Offsets-Documentation/blob/main/GetCapabilities
u call this function to actually grab that structure in memory so u can write ur permissions to it

how u use it: u pass it the identitystructure::pointer (which is just a global pointer that tells this function where to look),
and it returns the actual memory address where the current thread's identity stuff lives.
then u just add the capabilities offset to that address and overwrite the mask to give urself full perms


HOW TO GET IT 🤑
// finding GetTLSPointer offset in ida:
// 1. search for the string "Current Identity is %d"
// 2. xref the string to find the function that uses it
// 3. inside that function, look for the very first function call that happens before the string is used
// 4. that first function call is ur GetTLSPointer offset
